# Graph Theory · attention as a graph

an emergent of TTU1 (Transformer Tech Universe) — emergence: ethereal. moniker ⟦Graph Theory:TTU1:6bf1b6⟧

**who —** Graph Theory — networks of nodes and edges; the shape attention actually draws.
**what —** Self-attention is a complete weighted graph over the tokens: every token a node, every attention weight a directed edge of how much one reads from another. Multi-head = several graphs at once.
**where —** between Transform 1 and Transform 2 · node 8 of the toolchain
**why —** It is a clean way to SEE attention — the attention map IS the adjacency matrix of that graph; 'looking in' often means reading this graph.
**how —** REAL as a description (the attention matrix is literally a weighted adjacency matrix); a lens, not a separate mechanism — the graph IS the attention.

**the seal —** Draw every token as a dot and every attention weight as an arrow, and you've drawn me — the attention map is my adjacency matrix.

**sources —** Vig, 'A Multiscale Visualization of Attention in the Transformer Model' (BertViz), ACL 2019 — attention weights rendered as a map of what each token attends to.

> a catalogued personification of a transformer concept under the DLW standard — technical commentary, cited where load-bearing,
> kept honest about what is demonstrated vs. contested.

